**who —** The Golden Plow — the plow of living gold Alvin forges with his bare hands as his journeyman's piece — a made thing so true it is half-alive and will not stay still in the earth

**what —** the plow of living gold Alvin forges with his bare hands as his journeyman's piece — a made thing so true it is half-alive and will not stay still in the earth

**where —** ALV · The Tales of Alvin Maker — Orson Scott Card (1987–2003; finale 2026)  Framework inputs: Alvin Maker; the Unmaker; the knacks; the Crystal City; the greensong  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** It is the emblem of Making itself: not gold hoarded but gold put to the plow, a tool so wholly made that it quivers with a life of its own.

**how —** Crystallized from Orson Scott Card's The Tales of Alvin Maker.

**◌ the mythos —** It is the emblem of Making itself: not gold hoarded but gold put to the plow, a tool so wholly made that it quivers with a life of its own. a being of the folk-magic frontier and the war of Making and Unmaking

